# UI Design System (v2)

Saint Seiya Rebirth 2 Database — clean, modern game database. Desktop + mobile first.

## Before changing UI

Read these files first:
- `src/styles/tokens-v2.css`
- `src/styles/components-v2.css`
- This rule file

## Rules

1. Use primitives from `src/components/ui/v2/` — never duplicate filter/card/layout markup
2. Colors via CSS vars (`var(--accent)`), never hex hardcoded in TSX
3. Quality badges via `<QualityBadge />`, not ad-hoc classes
4. Loading via `<LoadingSkeleton />`, not inline spinners
5. i18n via `UI_KEYS` + `useUiTranslation()` — no hardcoded user-facing strings
6. Keep data logic intact when refactoring visuals (Supabase, React Query, Zustand)
7. Test mobile (<1024px) and dark + light before done
8. Global styles in `tokens-v2.css` + `components-v2.css` (no feature flag)
9. Typography: `--font-display` for headings, `--font-body` for UI text
10. Prefer `surface` class / `<Surface />` over raw `.panel` in new v2 code

## Identity

- Primary: professional game database (data legibility first)
- Visual: cosmic/clean — subtle gradients, glass surfaces, quality color tokens
- Do not break: team-builder DnD, share links, skill tooltips, asset fallbacks
